━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

0. DEFINITIONS

"StreamKernel" means the StreamKernel core runtime software,
including the pipeline orchestrator, inference engine, metrics
runtime, security layer, bundled sink/source/transformer
adapters, and all associated tooling governed by this license.

"You" (or "Your") means the individual or legal entity
exercising rights under this license.

"Organization" means a single legal entity, including its
wholly-owned subsidiaries.

"Internal Use" means use of StreamKernel solely to process
Your Organization's own data for Your Organization's own
operations, with no access to StreamKernel's functionality
granted to any third party.

"Substantially Powered By StreamKernel" means any product
or service in which StreamKernel serves as:
  (a) the primary stream processing or event pipeline runtime,
  (b) the inference orchestration or AI enrichment engine, or
  (c) a core execution component without which the product or
      service could not deliver its primary functionality.
The test is functional dependency, not code volume.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. PURPOSE

StreamKernel is provided as source-available software to
encourage adoption, evaluation, and internal use while
preserving the author's ability to monetize commercial
distribution and service offerings.

This license permits broad free use, including internal
production use at any scale, while requiring a commercial
license for external distribution and service offerings.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

2. PERMITTED USE (NO COMMERCIAL LICENSE REQUIRED)

You may, without a commercial license:

  (a) Use StreamKernel for development, evaluation, testing,
      proof-of-concept, and personal or educational purposes.

  (b) Use StreamKernel in Internal Use production deployments
      that process Your Organization's own data for Your
      Organization's own operations, at any scale.

  (c) Modify StreamKernel internally for Your own use.

  (d) Build custom plugins, connectors, transformers, sources,
      sinks, and extensions using the StreamKernel SPI.

  (e) Use StreamKernel in research, academic, or non-commercial
      open source projects.

  (f) Provide professional services, consulting, and
      implementation work to clients using StreamKernel,
      provided StreamKernel is not itself distributed or
      offered as a service to those clients.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

3. CUSTOM PLUGIN OWNERSHIP

Plugins, connectors, transformers, sources, sinks, or
extensions created by You using the StreamKernel SPI are
Your property. This license imposes no restrictions on
Your custom plugins, except where the StreamKernel core
runtime is redistributed alongside them.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

4. COMMERCIAL LICENSE REQUIRED

A commercial license is required to:

  (a) Offer StreamKernel, or any product or service
      Substantially Powered By StreamKernel, to third
      parties — whether hosted, managed, embedded, or
      delivered as SaaS.

  (b) Distribute StreamKernel, or any product incorporating
      StreamKernel, to external customers or users outside
      Your Organization.

  (c) Embed StreamKernel in a commercial product that is
      sold, licensed, or otherwise transferred to third
      parties.

  (d) Resell, sublicense, or relicense StreamKernel or any
      derivative of the StreamKernel core runtime.

  (e) Offer StreamKernel-as-a-Service, managed StreamKernel
      infrastructure, or hosted StreamKernel pipelines to
      paying or non-paying third parties.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

5. WHAT IS NOT RESTRICTED

For the avoidance of doubt, the following do not require
a commercial license:

  (a) Internal production use, including processing real
      business data in production systems, at any scale,
      for Your Organization's own operations.

  (b) Third-party consultants, system integrators, or
      contractors using StreamKernel to deliver
      implementation services to clients, provided
      StreamKernel is not itself distributed or offered
      as a service to those clients.

  (c) Building and distributing custom plugins that implement
      the StreamKernel SPI, provided the StreamKernel core
      runtime is not redistributed as part of that
      distribution.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

6. REDISTRIBUTION

Redistribution of StreamKernel source or binaries is
permitted only if:

  (a) This license is included in full and unmodified.
  (b) All copyright and attribution notices are preserved.
  (c) No license terms are removed or obscured.
  (d) The redistribution does not constitute a use requiring
      a commercial license under Section 4.

